quivalent to over three semi-trucks-full two to three times a week.\"  Per Royal Carribean CEO\'s blog.  http://www.nationofwhynot.com/blog/?p=825','71.141.241.141','0',0,1,'2010-01-18 16:24:05',NULL),(25,540,0,'Lucas Simmons','earthquake.relief@childhope.org','Child Hope / Maison De Lumiere (MDL) Orphanage is in desperate need of the following supplies for 50 children, staff and local feeding program that feeds hundreds of locals:\n\n50 bags of rice\n50 bags of beans\n6 cases of cooking oil\n25 cases of tomato sauce\nDiesel fuel - 200 gallons\n500 gallons of clean water\n\nAn emergency medical clinic has been set up at the orphanage, and the following medical supplies are needed:\n• Hydrogen Perioxide\n• Splints (all sizes)\n• Normal saline – IV bags & D5\n• Bleach\n• Foley Catheter & Foley Bags\n• Sterile drapes\n• Suture kits\n• Cydex – Sterilzation liquid\n• Gloves\n• Surgical brushes\n• Sterile water\n• Surigical gowns and masks\n• Pleural vac\n\nGPS Coordinates\n18 32 51.72N 72 17 07.62W\nDelmas 75, Rue Cassagnol #14, Port au Prince\n\nAmerican contact: \nLucas Simmons 619-277-5288, earthquake.relief@childhope.org\n\nContacts in Haiti\nBill Manassero 37349474\nSusette Manassero 36415161','76.191.174.106','0',0,1,'2010-01-18 20:50:07',NULL),(26,916,0,'Debbie LaPan','deblapan@msn.com','I am looking for Mirlande Jean, Antoinette (Matti) Amulca LaPan, and Emmanuel Thelemaque LaPan.  Are they there? We want to bring our children home.','173.81.14.233','1',0,1,'2010-01-18 21:28:06',NULL),(71,1030,0,'Kristine Brite','kbrite@gmail.com','Media, especially Associated Press have been closely following this. Last news reports from CNN and AP last night were that aid had come in the form of two HelpAge International reps. However, nursing residents were still dieing. The aid was not enough.\n\nAttempting to verify with HelpAge met with this tweet:\n@HomeCare4Senior @kristinebrite @KimDerstine Our emergency team were @ Municipal Nursing home last night and will be reporting bk 2 us today\n\nHowever, HelpAge is located in London and NGO would not explain what \"last night\" meant or if they were talking about the two aid workers or other efforts.','173.20.107.85','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 05:43:17',NULL),(28,397,0,'Jeremy Campbell','campjer@gmail.com','HelpTammyHelpHaiti.com water tower is still standing!  Use the GeoEye Imagery maps for Haiti to update satellite imagery post quake, then view these coordinates:\n\nhttp://earth.google.com/kmlpreview/#url=http%3A%2F%2Fbbs.keyhole.com%2Fubb%2Fubbthreads.php%3Fubb%3Ddownload%26Number%3D866479','64.118.23.66','1',0,1,'2010-01-18 22:48:48',NULL),(29,474,0,'Roldan\'s family','jproldan@aecirujanos.es','We found her! She\'s alive!!!\nGod bless you all!','88.19.63.253','1',0,1,'2010-01-19 01:18:20',NULL),(30,1070,0,'Shaun King','shaunking@courageous.tv','I have now sent several teams to this orphanage today. Details coming soon.','24.99.173.175','1',0,1,'2010-01-19 09:04:59',NULL),(31,827,0,'Sophie Martin','menclap3@yahoo.com','According to family members Gregory contacted a friend at 4:30 pm from his hotel room in the Hotel Montana.  I do not know the room number.  I can verify that neither his family nor his co-workers have heard from him since this contact.  I can also verify that his famioy has not heard from him since the quake struck.  I understand that a number of survivors have been pulled from the wreckage of the Hotel Montana. However, according to the media there are still a large number of people unaccounted for who were reported to have been at the Hotel Montana at the time of the quake.','200.108.21.70','1',0,1,'2010-01-19 10:14:24',NULL),(32,1079,0,'Shaun King','shaunking@courageous.tv','Have an address?','24.99.173.175','0',0,1,'2010-01-19 10:24:03',NULL),(33,389,0,'christy eckels','brendanowen@embarqmail.com','Children are ok now many if not all evacuated.','71.1.191.27','0',0,1,'2010-01-19 11:22:51',NULL),(34,764,0,'maria demee','mldemee@gmail.com','lOCATIOn - MUNICIPAL NURSING HOME: