ay be able to find Creole speakers, if telephone interpreting via the U.S. could be of any use to you.','69.249.88.140','0',0,1,'2010-01-19 23:50:31',NULL),(41,1119,0,'Stephen Nuchia','swn1@cox.net','My guys found the airhead well established, secure and efficient.  They accepted assignment to helicopter-born day missions to Leogane beginning AM 20 JAN, bringing food and medical supplies.','98.178.166.27','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 00:16:34',NULL),(42,1093,0,'Steve Nuchia','swn1@cox.net','There\'s a web page if you google it, places this im Mirebalais.','98.178.166.27','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 03:14:21',NULL),(44,1245,0,'Spydr','Spydrmedia@gmail.com','@SpyDrMedia for orto clinic:the place nearer where they can found drugs is Centre Dadadou (Delmas 3); Croix de Bouques\n\nCan contact paolo on www.Tilimi.com Channel 24.00 radio channel for emergency med\nMy info 773-698-0898 USA notified authorities via twitter as did many for you','67.149.50.229','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 09:34:35',NULL),(45,431,0,'Laura','metropolisdesign@comcast.net','We are looking for any information regarding the Ecole Notre Dame L\'Annunciation de Guerin in Leogane.  We house 30 elderly women at our compound off the main road.  We are looking for any information on the women, our staff, the sisters who run our school, Compagnes de Jesus, or our students.  Please contact me if you have any information.  Thank you.','71.195.48.231','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 10:25:30',NULL),(46,1219,0,'sam marting','cougar92s@gmail.com','do we know name or address of orphanage #1','174.99.0.98','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 11:08:39',NULL),(49,1244,0,'Mike','cuttersgoose@cpws.net','I hope that he is alive and well. I will keep him in my prayers.','76.9.167.143','1',0,1,'2010-01-20 17:29:42',NULL),(48,1210,0,'Caroline Meeks','caroline@solutiongrove.com','This is being retwitted in English\nhttp://twitter.com/ungaro/statuses/7990409970\nYoung man sent text message to FRANCE. He is buried in SOGEBANK (SIEGE SOCIAL) ROUTE DU #DELMAS PORT AU PRINCE.','130.64.184.54','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 15:29:23',NULL),(50,1342,0,'Chi Chi Valenti','chichi@jackiefactory.com','Location on this map is wrong. Correct address is 213 Avenue Jean Paul II, Haut-Turgeau\nCP 1408. Telephone # if working is 245 4523 or 4303','68.173.66.49','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 19:57:12',NULL),(51,936,0,'Rachelle Houde','rachelle.houde@gmail.com','Confirmation from contact that needs were delivered via email Jan. 19th @9:49 pm : \n\n\"Shaun just told me the water got to them. He said it was a mess there.\"','96.22.3.195','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 22:03:07',NULL),(52,625,0,'Lori Boyko','LoriBoyko@aol.com','I personally spoke with Tim Traynor @ Sacre Coeur Hospital on Tuesday night (Jan 19). They are a fully equipped hospital and only 1 of 2 Fully Accredited hospitals in Haiti (the other was in PAP and badly damaged). They are equipped and capable of taking care of the most severe trauma & surgical cases. They have done over 60 surgeries so far w/all patients still surviving! They have xrays and blood lab on site. They can continue to take patients as they are expanding rapidly in anticipation of great need! I\'m on twitter @LoriHCG They are @crudem_Haiti','71.234.27.242','0',0,1,'2010-01-20 23:14:51',NULL),(53,1342,0,'Chi Chi Valenti','chichi@jackiefactory.com','Report from Villa Manrese 1/19\n\nhttp://www.speroforum.com/a/25792/Quake-strikes-the-heart-of-the-church-in-Haiti','68.173.66.49','-1',0,1,'2010-01-21 00:08:00',NULL),(54,1105,0,'Al Macintyre','macwheel99@wowway.com','Map here is unclear as to precise location.  Here is maybe better: \nhttp://www.geonames.org/6201200/fontamara.html\n\nI am in contact with J-BIRD with Jacmel Airport Aid Station (Search & Medical Rescue from Seattle Washington), but not directly.  They were going to be in Leogane today, but were redirected to Petit Goave epicenter of latest quake, traveling on Canadian Helicopters.  I will relay this info to them.','68.179.179.122','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 00:52:13',NULL),(55,1276,0,'Mimi','ntaize@aol.com','Eric Belizaire can be reached at: 509-921-6408 in Croix-des-Bouquets.','151.188.105.237','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 08:37:33',NULL),(56,1397,0,'sociolingo','sociolingo@gmail.com','Further message 21 Jan 05.58pm\nmy name is Orel Ducasse. i am dehydrated and in need of food and water. Please:Rue lamarre impasse Mouzin next of Cine Capitol Port-auPrince\nvia @yveno76','87.112.98.194','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 11:59:15',NULL),(57,1018,0,'M300Ministries','info@m300ministries.org','PARENTS JUST APPEARED ON FOX NEWS JAN. 21, 2010 AROUND NOON EST. THEY ARE LOOKING FOR INFORMATION SPECIFICALLY ON THESE STUDENTS BY NAME. CONTACT FOX NEWS WITH ANY FURTHER INFO 4 PARENTS','75.90.21.60','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 12:16:37',NULL),(58,1455,0,'Caroline Meeks','Caroline@solutiongrove.com','another email on the same report:\nI am sending this email for Pastor Monoit Mercilus in Calebasse Haiti near Kenscoff\n \nThe name of my city calls Calebasse. Fort Jacques road number 20.   the name of the church is New Covenant church.I am between Kenscoff and Fort Jacques.  Let me give you another phone number again.565-8733,710-3221.\n \nHe oversees  7 churches/ schools in that area.  His home was spared and his Church had some damage.  But many of his church members homes have been completely leveled.  Yesterday another pastor brought him word that most of his church members homes were completely leveled as well.  They are drinking water out of a nearby stream.  They don’t have enough food or any bottled water.  They are running low on gas to full  a generator used to recharge batteries for cell phones.\n \nThey are in immediate need of food, water and clothes.  Many people are sleeping outside for two reasons, one most no longer have homes and because of fears of building falling in when they are sleeping.  Most of his  people have lost everything they had.\n \nPastor Monoit is a community leader in that area.  A lot of people and 8 other pastors turn to him for help with everything.  Every day more people are seeking him out for help and supplies are running low, they are desperate for some help or to just know that the relief effort is aware of their need.\n \nMonoit has a cell phone and a computer, we have been communicating every other day or so. \n \nHis email address is m.monoit@yahoo.com   Here are a couple of phone numbers\n \n509-901-8193\n \n509-565-8733\n \n509-710-3221\n \n \nThank you and God Bless You\n \nTerri Fox\nLoris, SC 29569\n843-504-2766\n843-503-3702','96.237.174.176','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 12:20:15',NULL),(59,1430,0,'Stephanie','little_steph_95@hotmail.com','We have not heard anything about how the orphanage is doing, or if anymore girls have died.  Please respond back on the situation of the building and the girls. My grandfather is the founder of the orphanage and we don\'t know anything since the aftershock. Please help.','70.54.71.121','2',0,1,'2010-01-21 13:44:07',NULL),(60,764,0,'Caroline Meeks','Caroline@solutiongrove.com','News report from CNN\nhttp://ac360.blogs.cnn.com/2010/01/21/video-haitis-seniors-need-help/?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed:+rss/cnn_ac360blog+(Blog:+AC360)&utm_content=Twitter','96.237.174.176','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 14:09:51',NULL),(61,1256,0,'christy eckels','brendanowen@embarqmail.com','spoke with person in camp directly still no help there.  They need medical supplies, tents, food water.  150 people taken in and around doctor\'s house. Doctor is out of supplies can\'t help wounded. please help asap','71.1.190.55','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 15:00:14',NULL),(62,1270,0,'Christy Eckels','brendanowen@embarqmail.com','Still have no help. Contact name is Amstyl Polycarpe phone 509-3647-7625.  NEED HELP ASAP! Doctor taking care of 150 people.','71.1.190.55','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 15:04:37',NULL),(63,1461,0,'josue','topjosue1123@yahoo.com','carre-four need help they dont have food and shelter and they need ur help please','96.246.9.220','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 16:27:29',NULL),(64,1441,0,'Jis','jiskavw@gmail.com','i have a location where you can get food, NO water, do you have a phonenumber for contact www.twitter.com/regelmama','82.95.155.102','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 16:39:38',NULL),(65,1441,0,'Amstyl Polycarpe','apolycarpe@gmail.com','give your phone number and/or email.','200.2.136.98','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 16:41:11',NULL),(66,1342,0,'Chi Chi Valenti','chichi@jackiefactory.com','A bit more information:\n\nemail for villa manrese is lavillamanrese@yahoo.fr\n\nFr. Garraud is running Villa Manrese effort and Joel Larivaux is in charge of logistics for food and water, both are on site (no cell info yet for either)\n\nFr. Jean-Guy has a working cell, have not been able to get through (may speak French only) (509 from outside Haiti) 342 444 21','68.173.66.49','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 17:03:23',NULL),(67,1470,0,'jinean','jrobinson@germonline.com','do you know exact coordinates? landmark or building?','24.99.56.187','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 17:27:25',NULL),(68,1219,0,'Caroline Meeks','Caroline@solutiongrove.com','no fuel, no water, no food, living outside buildings flat, 65 girls in one and 40 in another\nhttp://twitter.com/amieemccaffrey/status/8012995740','96.237.174.176','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 20:06:09',NULL),(69,1548,0,'aMBER','WAABZY@ROGERS.COM','Canadian news today warns of adopting children from Haiti orphaned due to quake for at least a year because many children separated from  families who may still be alive...........or have extended family','173.34.31.242','0',0,1,'2010-01-21 21:08:11',NULL),(72,1474,0,'@cait','scientaestubique@gmail.com','THIS IS OLD, NO LONGER VALID. SITE EVACUATED. NO FURTHER AID REQUIRED!!!! Do not retweet or repeat anywhere, please.','60.240.172.112','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 09:12:39',NULL),(73,604,0,'Laura','LauraRight1@me.com','I have been in contact with Hotel Villa Therese owner, Alain Villard, who has indicated that my brother, Rodney Rightenburg (U.S. Citizen) died when the hotel collapsed during the Haiti earthquake.','68.231.87.149','1',0,1,'2010-01-22 10:47:56',NULL),(74,1062,0,'Stephen Nuchia','swn1@cox.net','My guys are operating with the military vicinity of Leogane, first 3-5 planning to return home soon with 2-4 staying a few more days.  Recommend de-activating this resource record.  Thank you.','75.60.119.74','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 12:00:28',NULL),(75,1256,0,'christy eckels','christy.eckels@gmail.com','CONFIRMED by Amstyl Polycarpe occupant at camp that it has received medical help and supplies of food and water!!!','71.1.191.94','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 14:33:30',NULL),(76,1270,0,'christy eckels','christy.eckels@gmail.com','CONFIRMED by Amstyl Polycarpe occupant of camp that it has received medical help and food and water!','71.1.191.94','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 14:35:09',NULL),(77,1244,0,'Peter Fitzsimmoms','peter.fitsimmons@gmail.com','He has been our daughter\'s pysician for 22 years.  We so he is okay.','208.54.7.129','-1',0,1,'2010-01-22 15:06:42',NULL),(78,1651,0,'jinean','jrobinson@germonline.com','Does anyone have a phone or ability to email? Would like to contact you direcly.','24.99.56.187','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 15:46:00',NULL),(79,1617,0,'jinean','jrobinson@germonline.com','Have people on the ground there. Does anyone have a phone number or email access? Need to get in touch directly somehow.','24.99.56.187','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 15:47:46',NULL),(80,1649,0,'jinean','jrobinson@germonline.com','Have people on the ground there. Does anyone have a phone number or email access? Need to get in touch directly somehow.','24.99.56.187','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 15:48:30',NULL),(81,1615,0,'Caroline Meeks','Caroline@solutiongrove.com','More Details from another report:\nAmputation supplies urgently needed: Topical thrombin, Gelfoam, Hand-held bovie, Sliver nitrate, Osteotome\nhttp://livesayhaiti.blogspot.com/2010/01/need.html','96.237.174.176','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 15:48:41',NULL),(82,1615,0,'jinean','jrobinson@germonline.com','Do you still need this? Have people on the ground there. Does anyone have a phone number or email access? Need to get in touch directly somehow.','24.99.56.187','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 15:49:52',NULL),(83,1615,0,'Caroline Meeks','Caroline@solutiongrove.com','More details\n\nI think you maybe able to contact them through the blog comments: http://livesayhaiti.blogspot.com/2010/01/need.html\n\nWE IMMEDIATELY need this for a partial foot amputation:\n\n*Topical thrombin\n*Gelfoam\nHand-held bovie\nSliver nitrate\nOsteotome\n\nThe first two are musts. If anyone in Haiti has this and can tell us where to meet you or get it, we will help 18 year old Bernard with it ... and be eternally grateful to you. We need it by tomorrow, Saturday. We are 3 miles from the airport in Tabarre -- Clercine area. We can meet someone at the Deli Mart store or they can bring it to us at Rue Gelin which is a left off of Clercine --- past Kenz Oktobe on Clercine.','96.237.174.176','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 15:53:26',NULL),(84,764,0,'Caroline Meeks','Caroline@solutiongrove.com','11:32pmEST, 21 Jan, as reported by CNN: the nursing home has some food, but still require medical care.  All persons present are elderly, and they have been reported as, “slowly dying” and are sleeping outside.  Reporters from AP, CNN, and aid workers from HelpAge have brought them food.\n\nWe are still waiting to confirm GPS coordinates to try to get additional aid workers to the nursing home.\nUpdate 6:47pmEST 21Jan. from Washington Post:\n\nAn additional death: Jean-Marc Luis died Wednesday (20Jan.) night, from starvation.  HelpAge International was able to reach the facility today, and provide some protection and shelter outside.\n\n“Emergency programs coordinator Margaret Chilcott said the group will hire someone to do some cooking and get water points set up. Chilcott also noted that more caregivers were needed, and said she saw one man not eating despite his hunger, apparently because he couldn’t eat without help.”\n\nNeeds: Food and medicine for 84 survivors. 6 died in the earthquake and 2 have since died from hunger.\n\nSome aid has been provided, in the form of water from the Vivo Rio aid organization and a large bag of cooked rice from a concerned cleaner. Despite this, the residents have not eaten since Monday, 18 Jan.  There is also a desperate need for antibiotics and other medicine.','96.237.174.176','0',0,1,'2010-01-22 15:59:42',NULL),(85,1615,0,'Debi','debi@comber.us','Please call 509-3744-8718 to get these supplies to Jen Halverson.  THanks!','71.33.40.98','1',0,1,'2010-01-22 17:15:48',NULL),(86,163,0,'afkir','meniikhadija@hotmail.fr','Boucif  etait bien a l\'hotel Montana','78.240.68.4','1',0,1,'2010-01-23 11:20:45',NULL),(93,1767,0,'A N Dowden','andrew_dowden@softdesign.net.nz','http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&geocode=&q=18.544733,+-72.387972','121.73.60.39','0',0,1,'2010-01-24 20:28:37',NULL),(92,1773,0,'valerie','valaaa@hotmail.co.uk','Continuous prayes for HAITI! Thankyou','86.10.110.217','0',0,1,'2010-01-24 20:21:51',NULL),(90,1764,0,'redsalvavidas','jdc@redsalvavidas.org','estamos orgullosos de este aporte de la Armada colombiana para contribuir con el manejo de la crisis en Haití','190.125.158.228','0',0,1,'2010-01-24 06:14:34',NULL),(91,1244,0,'M.JOHNSON','MJPINK33@YAHOO.COM','I HAVE WORKED FOR DR. VAUGHTERS FOR OVER 10YRS. THIS IS TRULY HEARTBREAKING TO ALL HIS PATIENTS AS WELL AS HIS STAFF. EVERYONE PLEASE CONTINUE TO PRAY FOR OUR DOCTOR.','99.28.62.251','3',0,1,'2010-01-24 07:49:11',NULL),(94,1316,0,'A N Dowden','andrew_dowden@softdesign.net.nz','\'Rivière Froide\' School is in Ouest, Haiti\nhttp://www.maplandia.com/haiti/ouest/riviere-froide/\nhttp://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&geocode=&q=18.516671,-72.400007\n\nUS based News reports show rescue efforts have started at this location:\nhttp://www.jewishsf.com/article/full/41096/mission-to-haiti-turns-deadly-serious-for-bay-area-family/','121.73.60.39','0',0,1,'2010-01-25 02:08:19',NULL),(95,1316,0,'A N Dowden','andrew_dowden@softdesign.net.nz','Location should be changed to: 18.516671,-72.400007','121.73.60.39','0',0,1,'201