d escalating health and tuition costs. And heâll detail his efforts not only to better protect you and the American people at large, but also to restore Americaâs alliances and standing in the world.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Right after the Presidentâs address, weâll be open for questions on WhiteHouse.gov. So watch the President live at WhiteHouse.gov and stay tuned for a live chat immediately following with some of the Presidentâs top policy officials.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>As you know, when the President took office a year ago, he faced an array of historic challenges: an economy in freefall; job losses averaging almost 700,000 a month; a middle class under assault; two wars and badly frayed global alliances; and a staggering $1.3 trillion budget deficit.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Tonight, the President will address the progress weâve made to rescue the economy, rebuild the middle class, and restore our standing and leadership around the world. In addition, heâll outline whatâs needed to create a new foundation for prosperity and deliver on the change you and all Americans expect and deserve.</p></div>','http://www.ireport.com/docs/DOC-399771?ref=feeds/latest','2010-01-27 19:39:00'),(8367,7,11158,0,'America Your Quite A Lady - State of The Union','<div><p>The \"State\" of the Union depends on the heart of the people...WEÂ  the People create the \"State\" of the Union.Â  Our Leadership can steer thisÂ  Ship we call America, but her state depends our voice!!!</p></div>','http://www.ireport.com/docs/DOC-399882?ref=feeds/latest','2010-01-27 19:45:00'),(8366,7,11157,0,'The Stimulus Plan','<div><p>The stimulus plan was enforced to create new jobs but it sounds like most of it was used to develop excisting projects. I feel that most of it should have gone to companies that are expanding such as new facillitiesÂ  to provide jobs to college students that have graduated and is majoring in their field . Right now there is 